And as for the power of Love,Cant. 8. 6. Solomon will tell you it is as strong as death; the powerful workings whereof, are most emphatically represented by Paul to the Corinthians, 1 Cor. 13. 4, 5, 6, 7. Charity suffereth long, and is kinde; charity envieth not; charity vaunteth not it self, is not puffed up; doth not behave her self unseemly, seeketh not her own, is not easily provoked, thinketh no evil, rejoyceth not in iniquity, but rejoyceth in the truth;
